WEBVTT

00:01.678 --> 00:04.045
- "Mr. President." I'll never get
over saying that. - Jake.

00:04.113 --> 00:05.313
<i>Previously on "Scandal"...</i>

00:05.380 --> 00:06.080
How is she?

00:06.181 --> 00:08.147
She's good. Quiet.
Makes my job easy.

00:08.215 --> 00:09.749
She seems harmless.

00:09.817 --> 00:11.951
Olivia Pope
is not what she seems.

00:12.018 --> 00:13.720
Stay on her.

00:13.787 --> 00:15.287
- Yes.
- Yes?

00:15.356 --> 00:17.490
Yes, I will go out with you.

00:17.558 --> 00:19.091
(Fitz) They're running
a damn dally

00:19.159 --> 00:21.293
of the most glaring failure
of my presidency,

00:21.362 --> 00:23.295
while we for all apparent
purposes do nothing.

00:23.364 --> 00:25.297
You are doing everything
to get those hostages back safe.

00:25.365 --> 00:26.631
It's not your fault

00:26.699 --> 00:27.967
the intelligence
simply isn't there.

00:28.034 --> 00:29.701
These are the hostages.

00:29.769 --> 00:31.536
Their C.I.A. files were on
Wendy's flash drive.

00:31.604 --> 00:33.939
So Albatross, the mole,
the man who killed Wendy...

00:34.007 --> 00:36.141
He's the one who leaked
their names to the terrorists.

00:36.209 --> 00:38.477
That's him. That's the guy
who wanted what Wendy stole!

00:38.544 --> 00:40.411
That's the guy who killed her!
That's him on the tv!

00:40.479 --> 00:42.413
That is him!

00:42.481 --> 00:44.515
(Projector and camera shutter
clicking)

00:44.583 --> 00:46.885
- Mom, I'm starving.
- I think daddy ordered some pizza.

00:46.952 --> 00:48.920
- Ham and pineapple?
- Phil, the wireless is down again.

00:48.988 --> 00:51.022
Yeah, it's been acting funny
all night.

00:51.090 --> 00:53.091
- Emmett, set the table, would you?
- Dad, ham and pineapple?

00:53.158 --> 00:55.326
I have to look at this proposal
before the west coast goes down.

00:55.394 --> 00:57.327
-Try turning it off and turning it on.
- Dad?

00:57.395 --> 00:58.728
- What?
- What'd you get on the pizza?

00:58.796 --> 01:00.297
Ham and pineapple's gross.

01:00.365 --> 01:02.065
It's Hawaiian. Insult
their culture, why don't you?

01:02.133 --> 01:03.767
Hey. I got pepperoni.
Everybody's happy.

01:03.834 --> 01:04.968
- Ew.
- Gross.

01:05.036 --> 01:06.770
See what I deal with?
Come here.

01:06.837 --> 01:08.505
Mm. Thank you.
(Doorbell rings)

01:08.572 --> 01:09.739
(Emmett) Pizza's here.

01:09.807 --> 01:12.775
- Here's a $20.
- Give 'em a tip.

01:17.547 --> 01:19.649
(Shouting questions at once)

01:19.716 --> 01:20.116
(Man) Are you aware
of your mother's past?

01:21.217 --> 01:22.851
- Dad!
- (Projector and camera shutter clicking)

01:22.853 --> 01:24.253
(Man) Did your mother tell you
about the affair she had?

01:24.254 --> 01:27.689
We are at the home of Ryocorp
C.E.O. Sarah Stanner...

01:27.757 --> 01:29.524
The married woman accused
of having an affair

01:29.591 --> 01:32.392
with Murray Randall, President
Grant's recently announced

01:32.460 --> 01:33.494
-  supreme court nominee. 
- The alleged extramarital affair

01:33.562 --> 01:36.131
happened 15 years ago
when Randall was

01:36.198 --> 01:38.033
Stanner's Professor
at Harvard law...

01:38.100 --> 01:39.267
Confirmation hearings
have become a battleground

01:39.335 --> 01:40.735
for partisan wrangling,

01:40.803 --> 01:42.304
<i>and if this is what</i>
<i>the democrats meant</i>

01:42.371 --> 01:43.871
<i>by, quote, "vetting thoroughly,"</i>

01:43.939 --> 01:45.439
<i>I'd say they've made good</i>
<i>on their threat.</i>

01:45.506 --> 01:48.108
Is it true? What they're
saying about mom?

01:48.176 --> 01:49.810
No, sweetie, of course not.

01:49.877 --> 01:51.878
When you have an important
job like your mom's,

01:51.947 --> 01:54.048
sometimes people...
Try to tear you down.

01:54.115 --> 01:55.916
Tell your brother to brush
his teeth and wash up for bed.

01:55.984 --> 01:58.218
No tv, no computer...
Not tonight, okay?

01:58.286 --> 02:00.186
Um... yes, right.

02:00.254 --> 02:01.921
Um, let me just grab a...

02:01.989 --> 02:03.456
<i>But it certainly</i>
<i>has provided...</i>

02:03.523 --> 02:06.259
O-okay, thank you.
I will. Bye.

02:06.327 --> 02:07.927
What'd the lawyer say?

02:07.995 --> 02:11.264
She's sending someone in
named Olivia Pope.

02:11.332 --> 02:14.200
(Projector and camera shutter clicking)

02:14.268 --> 02:17.570
sync and corrections by bellows
www.addic7ed.com

02:17.637 --> 02:19.271
(Projector and camera shutter clicking)

02:21.641 --> 02:23.408
(Projector and camera shutter clicking)

02:26.312 --> 02:27.546
(Door opens) Sorry I'm late.

02:27.614 --> 02:28.981
I would have called,
but I was in a meeting.

02:29.048 --> 02:31.584
Don't worry. I've been keeping
myself entertained.

02:31.651 --> 02:33.885
Oh.
This one is truly special.

02:33.953 --> 02:36.588
Well, Yasmin was
a one-in-a-million kind of girl.

02:36.655 --> 02:39.090
She loved long walks,
dry climates, spitting.

02:39.157 --> 02:42.460
(Cell phone chimes)

02:42.528 --> 02:45.329
(Sighs) Let me guess.

02:45.397 --> 02:47.765
That means that we are not
having dinner, doesn't it?

02:47.833 --> 02:49.332
It's work.
I have to go.

02:51.035 --> 02:52.536
I was going to bring
this up over dinner,

02:52.604 --> 02:55.438
but I guess now I won't
have a chance, so...

02:55.507 --> 02:57.007
What do you know about

02:57.074 --> 02:58.909
the Kashfari hostage situation?

02:58.977 --> 03:01.545
I work in military
intelligence.

03:01.613 --> 03:03.446
We're all pretty familiar
with it. Why?

03:03.515 --> 03:05.347
I came across some information
that might help.

03:05.415 --> 03:07.517
- You came across it?
- You can't tell anyone it came from me,

03:07.584 --> 03:09.284
and you can't bring it
to the C.I.A.

03:11.788 --> 03:13.155
I don't have the authority
to just show up

03:13.223 --> 03:14.524
with something like that.

03:14.591 --> 03:16.258
And aren't you hooked up

03:16.326 --> 03:17.326
pretty good
with the White House?

03:17.394 --> 03:18.794
I can't go that route.

03:18.862 --> 03:20.896
- And you can't tell me why.
- It could help.

03:20.963 --> 03:23.331
I wouldn't bring it to you
otherwise.

03:24.534 --> 03:25.834
I'll see what I can do.

03:27.336 --> 03:29.404
Are you sure you've got
to go back to work?

03:29.471 --> 03:31.907
I could come over, flip through
some of your photo albums.

03:31.974 --> 03:33.341
Yearbooks, maybe...
It's only fair.

03:33.409 --> 03:34.776
Maybe next time?

03:34.844 --> 03:36.444
- So there's gonna be a next time?
- (Laughs)

03:36.512 --> 03:38.345
I like the sound of that.

03:38.413 --> 03:40.180
(Door closes)

